17e3f3fe-66d2-4098-9f6f-cd13d86d6bc0	coaching-conversation-prep	1	than including the employee's name or identifying details. The AI doesn't need to know who the person is to help you prepare for the conversation. ## Power Follow-Up Options - "Help me practice by role-playing as the other person" - "What am I not thinking about?" - "Give me an opening sentence I could actually say" - "What's the strongest case against my approach?" - "Simplify this — what are the two or three things I actually need to remember?" ## Common Difficult Conversation Types in HHS **Performance issues:** Focus on specific behaviors and their impact, not personality. Be clear about expectations going forward. Document the conversation. **Delivering bad news (to staff, clients, community):** Lead with the fact. Explain why. Acknowledge the impact. Offer what support is available. Be honest about uncertainty. **Pushing back on leadership:** Focus on impact and risk, not personal disagreement. Come with a counter-proposal, not just a rejection. Make the stakes clear. **Team conflict:** Separate the behavior from the person. Focus on shared goals. Avoid triangulating through others. 	[0.006246709,0.08671756,0.029661922,-0.039978724,0.0042870063,0.004298579,0.024894413,0.07831604,0.007182655,-0.10029062,-0.0758413,-0.03077359,-0.08419526,-0.02106249,0.027281204,0.07360901,0.070576504,0.00087256846,-0.04103723,0.011411961,0.007519745,-0.0070516723,-0.0059166,0.034176666,-0.108082876,0.026197912,0.053443782,-0.0355098,-0.043972813,0.004441617,0.00771908,-0.08334615,0.034374934,0.0496341,-0.07138574,0.089632146,-0.038427193,0.06709003,0.08289521,-0.014253696,-0.08825564,-0.031075004,0.027962202,-0.02528139,0.048844445,-0.065773405,-0.0013687625,0.01737884,-0.014720976,0.03177741,-0.13976935,-0.03076339,-0.014763476,0.09378594,0.018626256,0.051941592,0.014134298,0.058665883,0.05241274,-0.014202535,-0.006329536,-0.056410946,0.029560491,-0.024053926,-0.06200769,0.056305375,-0.01463649,-0.0016296036,-0.