1f2be00b-a461-49dd-8922-7a86f185b1e3	aps-prompts	0	# APS and Adult Protective Services Prompts for HHS Managers ## Important Data Safety Note Adult Protective Services involves vulnerable clients with sensitive health, financial, and personal information. APS cases involve allegations of abuse, neglect, or exploitation — all of which are highly confidential. Before using AI for any APS-related task, run a Red/Yellow/Green assessment. Client names, case numbers, diagnoses, financial information, and specific case details are Red — never include them in AI prompts. Use generalized descriptions and hypotheticals for any task involving specific client situations. ## Policy and Regulatory Tasks (Green) **Welfare and Institutions Code interpretation:** "Explain [specific WIC code section] in plain language for APS supervisors. What does this require us to do? What discretion do we have? Are there common misunderstandings?" **Understanding adult abuse categories:** "Describe the different types of elder and dependent adult abuse under California law in plain language. What distinguishes physical abuse from neglect? What is self-neglect and how is it different?" **Cross-reporting requirements:** "Explain cross-reporting requirements for APS in California. When must we report to law enforcement? When to Licensing? What are the timelines?" ## Supervisory and Management Tasks (Green-Yellow) **Case consultation structure (without identifying details):** "Help me create a framework for APS supervisory case consultations. What questions should supervisors ask to assess risk? What factors indicate a case needs escalation?" **Safety planning concepts:** "What are evidence-based approaches to safety planning with self-neglecting adults who refuse services? What does the research say about effective engagement strategies?" **Difficult conversations with clients:** "Help me prepare for a conversation with an adult client who is refusing services but appears to be at significant risk [describe scenario type without identifying details]. What approaches might be effective? What should I avoid?" ## Leadership and Communication Tasks (Green) **Stakeholder education:** "Draft talking points for a presentation to [hospital	[-0.030325245,0.05803272,-0.016884878,0.006916676,-0.040603872,0.045742393,0.011696764,0.035194304,0.020564295,0.04491292,0.04507521,-0.014225245,0.017807703,0.022190865,-0.0055107963,0.06642935,0.08304112,-0.058314003,-0.07505258,0.032796614,0.041634575,0.0457394,-0.0116010755,-0.006563283,-0.1362967,0.019556385,-0.01743898,-0.061155193,-0.070272386,0.018659739,0.02946159,-0.03268545,0.067912534,-0.005594749,0.026578756,0.055828396,0.039463922,0.023442533,-0.0161198,-0.0026683067,-0.068778776,-0.00029570528,0.018474394,0.016596453,-0.032049593,-0.079841994,-0.06836221,-0.030885367,-0.03966394,-0.051683825,-0.058485944,-0.03588066,0.026118373,0.11395236,-0.05707056,-0.036704455,0.079987675,-0.013880909,-0.034357797,-0.0016704388,-0.041800976,0.02215468,0.04109467,0.011549047,-0.010128931,0.061269656,-0.04062098,-0.05007099,0.042890225,0.016750276,-0.03923496,-0.01892721,-0.011742505,0.018869475,0.028473178,0.017637286,-0.023152279,0.038801495,0.14074521,-0.14805822,0.052478533,0.05476777,-0.043987066,0.07215376,-0.054065563,0.021407146,-0.019456014,0.018892916,0.012266625,-0.0010067566,0.03198564,-0.04126405,0.052490607,-0.06286308,0.11999686,-0.014823456,-0.0508963,-0.10929945,-0.07732525,-0.034456316,0.01654192,-0.035423063,-0.0031355452,-0.021200698,-0.05842533,-0.005992671,-0.054410275,-0.040205434,-0.05194029,0.069734044,0.018198851,0.035405673,-0.057242125,-0.07229584,0.036381967,-0.002173237,-0.0064967335,0.032551795,0.050274353,0.014705932,0.02975412,-0.015989617,0.0189332,0.019132992,0.040326815,0.012186898,-0.073741734,6.1415227e-33,0.07310307,0.038455326,-0.057131242,0.03127872,-0.0049165767,-0.024608715,0.01811366,-0.01907737,0.010418614,-0.0028439935,0.034030084,0.0657778,0.054279506,-0.13268997,-0.04904251,0.009458212,