8e666836-38c2-481b-af36-a5f10795474b	cps-prompts	0	# CPS and Child Welfare Prompts for HHS Managers ## Important Data Safety Note Child welfare work involves highly sensitive client information. Before using any AI tool for CPS-related tasks, run a Red/Yellow/Green assessment. Client names, case numbers, dates of birth, identifying addresses, and specific case details are Red — do not include them in AI prompts. Many tasks can be accomplished with hypothetical or generalized descriptions that don't identify specific clients or families. ## Policy and Regulatory Tasks (Green) **Summarize an ACL or policy update:** "Summarize this CDSS All-County Letter in plain language for CPS supervisors. Include: what's changing, what we're required to do differently, key deadlines, and any ambiguous requirements that need legal or policy clarification." **Explain a regulation to staff:** "Explain [specific regulation or requirement] in plain language for frontline CPS workers. Use examples that would be familiar in a CPS context. Avoid jargon." **Prepare for a state audit or review:** "Help me prepare for a [CDSS/federal] review of our [specific program area]. What documents and data should we gather? What questions are reviewers likely to ask? What are common findings in this area?" ## Supervisory and Management Tasks (Green-Yellow) **Staff training topics:** "Generate 5 training scenarios for new CPS workers focused on [specific area — initial assessment, safety planning, family engagement, documentation]. The scenarios should reflect common challenges without including real case details." **Performance feedback framework:** "Help me draft a framework for giving CPS supervisors feedback on their coaching of workers. What dimensions matter most? What behaviors indicate strong supervisory practice?" **Meeting agenda for a complex situation:** "Create an agenda for a [CFT/TDM/supervisory consultation] focused on a general situation where [describe scenario type without client details]. What topics should we cover to be thorough?" ## Leadership and Communication Tasks (Green) **Community or stakeholder communication:** "Draft a	[-0.071382076,0.0737268,-0.039594688,0.008314833,0.040132258,0.058633953,0.037092805,0.047293115,-0.065941624,0.049939048,-0.01102721,-0.09399283,-4.6655434e-05,0.03474142,-0.012525319,0.072649956,0.12512513,-0.033321373,-0.055325035,-0.00721003,0.07508219,-0.018263394,0.001758882,0.002309249,-0.12991592,0.04245964,0.0041031563,-0.041801084,-0.107329465,0.0097478395,-0.005324341,-0.01948687,0.028520254,-0.0058844974,0.041511223,0.10129246,0.024177846,0.048399232,0.007340734,-0.0010177371,-0.085913554,0.021199755,0.0017974911,0.020309223,-0.010218188,-0.09695101,-0.012103754,-0.03730834,-0.07495396,0.00034923622,-0.0681436,-0.06341013,0.019595407,0.034965653,0.010037851,-0.005345731,0.0575449,-0.033795953,-0.025707752,-0.08559835,-0.07143587,0.018003946,-0.025564574,-0.018752921,0.03468755,0.038410448,-0.09505531,0.016658762,0.012545983,-0.018545058,-0.091310084,0.034230854,0.0023572252,0.032369845,-0.0011875465,0.04055001,-0.0041157454,0.080338664,0.06306879,-0.188227,0.015846208,0.0987672,0.0015134934,0.037821133,0.0026288307,0.01697526,0.02200325,0.0059007914,-0.0038450013,0.04639423,0.06876346,-0.04221698,0.10211011,-0.0632709,0.064016856,0.012760879,-0.0050827465,-0.07154597,-0.001636137,-0.0051323418,0.07234587,0.007313119,0.020131426,-0.03878888,-0.08514853,-0.008754083,-0.014613797,-0.030661233,-0.0744535,0.01006191,-0.014505883,0.04539713,-0.09410154,-0.064387,0.03068932,-0.04447541,0.045845777,0.0017036843,-0.0031362919,0.03198272,-0.010064006,-0.022275744,-0.0050250012,0.010324073,0.028660623,-0.02021189,-0.041401334,5.3569342e-33,-0.03083734,0.032786515,-0.047004487,0.0752561,0.021516943,-0.0068761436,0.046446152,0.04543013,-0.016050743,0.03351192,-0.013427952,0.03193531,0.004069979,-0.053166565,-0.06189111,-0.048082042,-0.023356253,0.0770268,-0.061896283,0.034311786,0.0031593821,-0.0071932976,-0.021002794,0