f4b81a37-7c7f-4370-b194-00e3ae3a8c33	aidn-feedback-model_v20260423c	0	# AIDN Feedback Model **Corpus Document | Category: Methodology** **Retrieval targets: feedback, coaching conversation, difficult conversation, performance conversation, praise, recognition, corrective feedback, developmental feedback, motivational feedback** --- ## What AIDN Is AIDN is a four-step feedback framework for leaders who need to deliver feedback that changes behavior or reinforces it. It works for both motivational feedback (praise and reinforcement) and developmental feedback (corrective and performance-related). The acronym stands for: - **A — Action**: The specific, observable behavior you saw or heard. - **I — Impact**: The consequence of that behavior on people, teams, clients, or outcomes. - **D — Desired Outcome**: The observable standard of what you need to see going forward. This is the 20,000-foot view — the destination, not the directions. - **N — Next Steps**: The concrete actions both parties will take between now and the next conversation, including the accountability mechanism. AIDN evolved from the AID model (Action, Impact, Do), which is widely used in management training. AID's third step — "Do" — combines two different functions into one: defining the target state and establishing accountability. That works for simple feedback, but breaks under pressure. When the stakes are high, leaders need to clearly separate "here is the standard" from "here is what happens next." AIDN makes that separation explicit. The framework does not change based on severity. The weight of the Next Steps changes. A light conversation ends with "let's check in next month." A serious one ends with "we'll evaluate whether this role is the right fit." Same four steps. Different gravity in the N. --- ## How to Coach With This Framework Default to coaching mode. When someone brings a feedback situation, do not draft the full AIDN script for them. Walk them through it: 1. Ask what they observed — help them	[-0.09179531,-0.010112622,0.02973478,0.016523259,0.021757217,0.02536909,0.019436512,0.067830816,0.07008977,-0.0041339216,-0.021936275,-0.0015558214,-0.0022482397,0.05228677,-0.01613115,0.015326746,0.053998385,0.019685525,-0.12677903,-0.0015550347,0.08981303,-0.014880577,0.08636212,0.046578802,-0.11570304,-0.0012842036,-0.033107273,-0.01659514,0.02921373,-0.06149032,-0.00045546924,-0.04609874,0.03479956,0.021459244,-0.12734202,0.1364497,0.01411424,0.030624803,-0.07033707,-0.055258445,-0.028658368,-0.012735607,0.030256415,-0.019086825,0.05110561,-0.08405397,-0.05375213,-0.014118002,-0.10219888,-0.031619523,-0.08481184,-0.08566935,0.00022726117,0.059514344,0.045341272,0.07112642,0.053592037,-0.010849455,-0.020157246,-0.059673246,-0.018173039,-0.024980037,-0.124130495,-0.0059511987,-0.0245614,0.0069817356,-0.07366831,0.047196813,-0.037466437,0.0054426366,-0.00973299,-0.07049635,0.04795741,-0.069661625,0.02733071,0.06910267,0.03341538,0.06501082,0.059755694,-0.036315523,-0.0039616884,0.043814413,0.030148901,-0.015805533,-0.057534568,-0.08162308,0.035265766,0.013323163,0.05614507,0.09772861,-0.0052750707,0.047742464,-0.027078161,0.017718568,0.011972341,0.04962599,-0.019794187,-0.075942785,-0.025068609,0.09625989,0.06421418,0.052519426,-0.012412098,-0.05715088,-0.049192954,-0.07044387,-0.025981287,-0.0076742843,0.014334091,-0.0061147287,-0.08038589,-0.015956087,-0.05505638,0.025561921,0.028567597,0.005930393,-0.07559141,-0.0016081636,0.01971094,0.017830849,0.082210414,-0.032590173,0.024238134,0.0015113147,0.049658876,0.009427144,-0.033050496,-1.5289934e-33,0.054972094,-0.008935873,0.012331669,0.06428948,0.020303927,-0.010476243,0.018622426,0.02712336,-0.051866777,-0.0032932595,-0.016669488,0.015799826,0.065436564,0.058701575,-0.011411968,-0.058417235,-0.045449544,0.04230418,-0.0458371,0.047616556,0.05502404,0.02325543,0.012370295,0.012182354,0.05988796,-0.009378441,0.0043206294,-0.0007770695,-0.07388761,0.0016757445,-0.030501755,-0.031398706,-0.004626587,-0.06602