ae2d7c2a-b23e-4814-a768-739c27b96e06	aidn-feedback-model_v20260423c	10	## Using AIDN for Motivational Feedback Motivational feedback builds confidence. Its purpose is to reinforce behavior you want to see more of and signal what good looks like. When using AIDN for praise and reinforcement: - **Action**: Be just as specific as you would be with developmental feedback. "Great job" is not motivational feedback. It is a pleasantry. Name exactly what they did. - **Impact**: Explain the specific positive consequence. Who benefited? What improved? What was the ripple effect? - **Desired Outcome**: Where do you want to see this behavior applied next? Motivational D is about expansion — taking a demonstrated strength and deploying it more broadly. - **Next Steps**: This might be a stretch assignment, a mentoring role, a leadership opportunity, or continued reinforcement. Motivational N tells the listener: your work has been noticed, and here is what it opens up. Motivational AIDN is not just "saying something nice." It is strategic reinforcement. When a leader consistently uses AIDN to recognize specific behavior and connects it to outcomes and opportunities, they create a culture where people know exactly what excellence looks like — because they have heard it described in precise, observable terms. --- ## Using AIDN for Developmental Feedback Developmental feedback builds competence. Its purpose is to change behavior that is not meeting the required standard. When using AIDN for corrective or performance feedback: - **Action**: Facts only. No interpretations, no character judgments, no blur words. - **Impact**: Draw out the listener's perspective first. Then share your own observation. This builds self-awareness and reduces defensiveness. If the listener identifies the impact accurately, they have already begun to own the problem. - **Desired Outcome**: Define the observable behavior you need to see instead. Be specific enough that the listener knows exactly what success looks like. This is collaborative —	[-0.07774973,0.012136847,0.04742865,-0.0009171035,0.023623474,0.02683012,0.06646842,0.09295706,0.031784717,-0.01282624,-0.03961737,-0.040182717,0.030885017,0.053707518,-0.046262365,0.05041625,0.07965979,0.08073322,-0.16595963,-0.060437392,0.06674211,-0.047701776,0.056873005,-0.00755929,-0.111724645,0.024530577,-0.0057014655,0.021815024,0.08497381,-0.066739805,0.0056889514,-0.0027325945,0.04285616,-0.014456192,-0.10416692,0.079466954,-0.03589733,0.083583444,-0.030646412,-0.08645032,-0.0014925216,0.0055685067,0.05238403,-0.049815767,0.013353647,-0.15787634,0.009223585,-0.019520555,-0.07503025,-0.0072723255,-0.0550407,-0.109498195,-0.015181003,-0.009693483,0.030811088,0.09033555,0.031000152,0.003312775,-0.060975824,-0.086011015,0.015898373,-0.015372701,-0.06783118,-0.03903276,0.008300344,0.017769238,0.005613506,0.057123583,-0.0438606,0.006080108,0.03357434,-0.04339753,0.035462923,-0.070564866,0.06053398,0.021165432,-0.0033255063,0.03162094,0.05493328,-0.010722548,0.034379773,0.052173756,-0.00918932,0.0054352814,-0.046553686,-0.070664555,0.03158346,-0.034487523,0.06709082,0.06497467,-0.01162973,0.05432059,-0.08369974,-0.014410341,0.012731481,-0.013663284,-0.029707829,-0.057113383,-0.0068515544,0.110255785,0.05958012,0.04099012,-0.038742978,-0.03266429,-0.027215159,-0.042027097,-0.047639564,0.005404986,0.011885621,-0.014733514,-0.07204979,-0.029031461,-0.07010503,0.05098342,0.037591945,0.020199537,-0.06622671,-0.016528523,-0.013357067,-0.05346021,0.14226863,-0.057262816,0.0361247,0.07523645,0.019152245,-0.027175456,-0.032175366,3.3616997e-33,0.03185101,0.019233268,0.026442409,0.027202375,0.040678438,-0.043145776,0.021222042,0.0024412822,-0.061749924,-0.03567004,-0.021956488,0.06384754,0.06246429,0.07581406,0.022027176,-0.01939308,-0.066421345,0.01968267,-0.062407993,0.06484192,0.05692596,0.00877131,-0.023479845,-0.02630544,0.031957,-0.060115814,0.02653828,0.012460066,-0.08755097,0.0056908107,-0.0042186887,-0.038727853,0.013839885,-0.06