c2a646bc-5f6a-414d-bc1f-688d6b296706	aidn-feedback-model_v20260423c	12	becomes mutual. ### Managing Up When giving feedback to a leader above you, lead with Impact on you or your team, then describe the Action that caused it. Reversing the order can feel less confrontational when managing up. Desired Outcome becomes a request: "What would help me and my team is..." Next Steps are proposals: "Would you be open to..." ### Skip-Level When a senior leader gives feedback to someone two or more levels below, Next Steps should always include the listener's direct supervisor in the accountability loop. Skip-level feedback that bypasses the chain of command undermines the middle manager and creates confusion. --- ## How AIDN Differs from Other Feedback Models - **AID** (Action, Impact, Do): AIDN's predecessor. AID's third step has been interpreted variously as "Do differently," "Development," "Desired Behaviour," and "Desired Outcome" across different practitioners. AIDN adopts the Desired Outcome framing and adds a fourth step — Next Steps — to separate the target state from the accountability mechanism. This separation is what allows AIDN to scale from a two-minute hallway conversation to a formal performance review without changing the framework. - **SBI** (Situation, Behavior, Impact): Ends at Impact with no forward-looking structure. Describes what happened and what it caused, but gives no framework for what comes next. - **COIN** (Context, Observation, Impact, Next Steps): The closest structural relative. Has Next Steps but lacks an explicit Desired Outcome step. Accountability without a clearly defined target. - **CEDAR** (Context, Examples, Diagnosis, Action, Review): Five steps. Coaching-heavy. Effective for complex situations but too heavy for routine feedback. AIDN delivers comparable rigor in four steps. - **Feedback sandwich** (Positive-Negative-Positive): Wraps criticism in false praise. Trains the listener to distrust positive feedback. AIDN treats motivational and developmental feedback as separate conversations — never blended. --- ## Preparation Checklist Before entering any	[-0.03985984,0.012006168,0.04640792,-0.014483179,0.043957524,0.00041089894,-0.06620559,0.051255763,0.05251628,0.005630445,-0.026400879,-0.013660252,0.03234978,0.008330014,-0.020160299,0.046596296,0.04842721,0.015370189,-0.1100163,-0.004330028,0.07268714,-0.03288391,0.071280874,0.027933301,-0.12263358,-0.028704418,-0.04674731,0.01476422,-0.008004256,-0.074699685,-0.019502383,-0.044494554,0.016195158,0.007098732,-0.11081739,0.10337678,0.011296217,0.05778173,-0.0777826,-0.043983746,-0.012009309,0.0452986,0.012379367,-0.060206585,0.016736062,-0.11669317,-0.0570556,-0.06206814,-0.10560869,-0.065221965,-0.06408322,-0.055894103,-0.013308499,0.037943803,0.017126726,0.07556433,0.081329204,-0.03574711,-0.021482902,-0.06379968,-0.052966785,-0.043336146,-0.09381268,-0.0353587,-0.006733594,0.029679073,-0.011245716,0.036277395,-0.016909301,0.07800529,0.023170682,-0.09079183,0.010830448,-0.08491308,0.033214476,0.03129614,2.3253235e-06,0.09713485,0.014948757,-0.059683528,-0.03666645,0.031398006,0.026521157,0.033275913,-0.040320642,-0.10111715,0.025670547,-0.015661689,0.068727575,0.096351154,-0.005225672,0.007646992,0.010503237,-0.015857909,0.037533555,0.0265465,-0.005175062,-0.060265306,-0.052243687,0.07738963,0.055057187,0.0388387,-0.030189497,-0.117407724,-0.005223388,-0.026873957,-0.011027039,-0.018060563,-0.045970034,-0.025652973,-0.038431205,-0.052823376,-0.03549233,-0.00037108525,0.065736845,0.04184184,0.0010497347,0.011230075,0.019217093,-0.04694163,0.11142215,-0.041529484,0.069438785,0.011555918,0.026564468,0.04063065,-0.014959201,6.1046246e-33,0.033967584,-0.016124144,-0.02454296,0.03263796,0.031013515,0.010800872,0.009549923,0.024603778,-0.08866066,0.011152572,-0.015969452,0.04261745,0.04903543,0.02087582,-0.06441705,-0.077628925,0.00310651,0.05634129,-0.068865895,0.016276497,0.02240292,0.00041744,-0.02453414,-0.031320464,0.04901276,-0.04538866,-0.02476