d36b9be7-2a69-4b5e-9681-454fa2c08bb1	aidn-feedback-model_v20260423c	13	complex situations but too heavy for routine feedback. AIDN delivers comparable rigor in four steps. - **Feedback sandwich** (Positive-Negative-Positive): Wraps criticism in false praise. Trains the listener to distrust positive feedback. AIDN treats motivational and developmental feedback as separate conversations — never blended. --- ## Preparation Checklist Before entering any AIDN feedback conversation, answer these questions: 1. Is my Action grounded in direct observation? Corroborated reports from others can support it, but if I have never personally observed the behavior, I am not ready. 2. Is my feedback timely? If the Action happened more than a week ago, the impact is significantly diminished. 3. Can I articulate the Impact in one or two sentences? If not, I have not thought it through. 4. Is my Desired Outcome observable? If I watched this person on video a month from now, would I know whether they achieved it? 5. Have I calibrated my Next Steps to the severity? First-time issue? Light check-in. Third conversation about the same pattern? Elevated accountability. 6. Am I prepared for denial, deflection, or defensiveness? 7. What is my intention? Am I entering this conversation to help this person succeed, or to vent frustration? If the latter, reschedule. --- ## Key Principles - **Feedback is about behavior, not character.** Every element of AIDN focuses on what a person did, not who they are. Character-based feedback triggers identity threat. Behavior-based feedback is specific, addressable, and non-threatening. - **Observable beats interpretive.** If it cannot be seen, heard, or measured, it does not belong in the conversation. - **Motivational and developmental feedback are separate conversations.** Never blend them. The feedback sandwich is discredited for a reason. - **The leader is a partner, not a judge.** AIDN is framed as a collaborative approach to a mutually agreed destination. Even at the most	[-0.024250396,-0.029113803,0.030841706,0.028518794,0.040440466,0.01796833,0.017661428,0.06903434,0.041121345,-0.005413933,-0.031472296,-0.07090258,-0.010995426,0.043243766,-0.105139636,0.0491019,0.100496575,0.014753658,-0.13664678,0.066924945,0.061853852,-0.04893543,0.07994581,-0.0018949627,-0.10153607,0.013823618,0.01873223,-0.006303477,-0.024994474,-0.08055037,-0.03205209,-0.041692827,0.01577726,0.021556491,-0.07264406,0.08719438,0.06796772,0.058942135,-0.02955796,-0.072678454,0.0026575748,-0.00906487,0.062392253,-0.06882334,0.0155345,-0.14209175,-0.024506995,-0.019976819,-0.13769884,-0.053985324,-0.09193488,-0.036468398,-0.0063199545,0.06735576,0.0049957414,0.03629475,0.03438299,0.04022139,-0.025103038,-0.01660114,-0.009880151,-0.03227169,-0.074920565,0.004073266,-0.0204184,0.10916028,-0.035783466,-0.02459689,0.009316764,0.059144396,-0.04188468,-0.020484786,0.021468539,-0.057221875,0.002969633,0.024576405,-0.0063635227,0.03873986,0.053072155,-0.055076994,0.029875902,0.039069146,0.0018991157,-0.032835852,-0.028708372,-0.11202754,0.044163384,0.04152789,-0.0006442684,0.08138978,0.01247285,0.05971159,0.005240621,-0.011406637,0.0326734,0.06262921,-0.076369405,-0.037898794,-0.018029805,0.08114708,0.045535814,0.047220003,-0.037973806,-0.045632176,-0.0295235,-0.026016688,-0.06638981,-0.008596521,-0.08087512,0.002439265,-0.07311454,-0.027883371,-0.03966122,0.030244572,0.0715176,0.038384758,-0.028202385,0.00051822414,0.021552682,0.0010605776,0.13980365,-0.04571781,0.060874686,0.025779998,0.054459047,0.0057761483,-0.027393054,4.5115885e-33,0.006945027,0.015754908,-0.043528907,0.05850493,-0.034339603,0.006918708,-0.0103706485,0.012066824,0.0058892188,0.018571474,0.015282858,0.016643435,0.06102032,0.0049873735,-0.019340767,0.0076659536,-0.0441813,0.035954654,-0.08622893,0.06036378,0.052085496,-0.02413755,-0.020215334,4.0013834e-05,0.017160539,-0.09967215,0.03534375,0.03557551,-0.10315488,-0.020763002,-0.05468973,-0.020449027,-0.0012126415,-0.04981377,0.029