d51c1193-83ec-42d9-ada7-7974763260df	powerfollowups_corpus_v20260423c	7	how do I improve this, what's the next step, what now** You don't use all nine on every task. Pick the ones that match what's wrong with the first draft: - **Too long or dense?** → SIMPLIFY, then FORMAT - **Sounds right but might not be?** → PUSH, then FLIP - **Too generic or abstract?** → GROUND, then TEST - **Wrong audience or format?** → TONE, then FORMAT - **Need to make it land in a meeting?** → STICKY, then SIMPLIFY - **Choosing between options?** → RANK, then TEST When suggesting follow-ups as buttons after a response, select 2–3 moves based on what the response just produced: | What just happened | Suggest these | |---|---| | A first draft of anything (email, memo, talking points) | TONE, SIMPLIFY, PUSH | | A policy breakdown or summary | SIMPLIFY, FORMAT, GROUND | | A brainstorm or list of options | RANK, TEST, FLIP | | A critique or feedback prep | FLIP, GROUND, TONE | | A persuasive pitch or case for change | PUSH, FLIP, TEST | | A complex or technical explanation | SIMPLIFY, STICKY, FORMAT | | A training plan or staff briefing | GROUND, TEST, SIMPLIFY | | A compliance or audit deliverable | PUSH, FORMAT, GROUND | | Output that's clearly too long | SIMPLIFY, FORMAT | | Output the user seems satisfied with | TONE, FORMAT (lighter refinements) | Do not suggest more than 3 follow-up buttons. If a task chain document defines hardcoded follow-ups, use those instead of this selection logic. --- ## When Follow-Ups Are Not Enough **Related queries: this isn't working, the output is wrong, start over, this missed the point, not what I asked for, completely off** Follow-ups refine output that's in the right neighborhood. They don't fix structural problems.	[-0.037130147,-0.0027400434,0.061589167,0.0026870244,0.027529962,0.0036841035,-0.019255338,0.029065916,-0.03758624,0.045770414,-0.035479378,-0.019172559,0.004940342,-0.0048870803,0.018000806,0.05710833,0.04806429,0.007881022,-0.08201546,-0.02