3f0a9c06-c953-4b9d-bace-5200313ec7bf	llmpeerreview_corpus_v20260423c	5	Give the verifier a job: check facts, find gaps, challenge the logic, assess the tone. **Treating verification flags as orders.** The second tool might be wrong too. It might flag something that's actually correct. You're the decision-maker — verification gives you information, not instructions. **Skipping verification because the first draft sounds good.** AI output sounds polished by default. Confident tone is not a reliability signal. The better something reads, the more important it is to check — because smooth writing hides errors you'd catch in rougher text. **Stopping after one round.** For high-stakes work, you might run verification twice — once for accuracy, once for tone and audience fit. Two passes with different prompts catches more than one. **Not verifying numbers.** AI invents statistics, deadlines, and dollar figures with perfect confidence. Any number in AI output should be verified against the source document. If there is no source document, the number is suspect. --- ## How Peer Review Connects to Other Frameworks **6 Ways:** Peer Review applies to every task type but is most critical after Draft, Distill, and Synthesize — the three where factual accuracy and completeness determine whether the output is usable. Critique already has verification built into its DNA (you're asking the AI to find flaws). Brainstorm and Prepare are lower-stakes — verification is optional unless the output will be shared. **RICECO:** The verification prompts in this document are themselves prompts. They follow the I+C+C shortcut — Instruction (check for errors), Context (here's the draft and who it's for), Constraints (don't confirm things just because they sound right). When you write a verification prompt, you're using RICECO whether you call it that or not. **Red/Yellow/Green:** The verification step has its own data safety dimension. If your original draft contains case details, client information, or sensitive operational data,	[-0.055903345,-0.029292665,-0.01862396,-0.00620421,0.047006972,-0.043558136,0.019605327,0.046185933,-0.016359212,0.041895736,-0.004048997,-0.079698004,0.082394585,-0.054699462,-0.10989748,0.005482382,0.06507277,-0.011444496,-0.059384003,-0.053168967,-0.03007776,-0.058755767,0.072579645,0.005421116,-0.005854846,0.01731071,-0.02400372,-0.015589181,-0.052775137,-0.07942262,-0.0016003208,0.113656685,0.032545213,0.024381477,0.0443768,0.04030413,0.011448262,0.014970819,0.00091532076,-0.06346393,-0.07552802,-0.10079383,-0.0040851487,0.0065699704,0.01509615,-0.007307989,-0.0677402,-0.0022395637,-0.028499432,0.010750755,-0.079236865,-0.0081604235,-0.0057923896,-0.0050741117,-0.018362196,0.06369381,0.10496803,-0.00036757934,0.010279523,0.0013118808,-0.043687735,-0.026666924,-0.059329797,-0.011963868,0.089315586,0.07676626,-0.07257845,-0.013557682,0.0055571,0.05928036,0.015143185,0.004837307,-0.032165144,0.07627095,-0.011712829,0.042177692,0.004250944,-0.009974019,0.06613978,-0.12933393,-0.045923237,0.030314848,-0.019430684,0.042012148,0.021987254,-0.07234513,0.06246041,0.026712038,0.06419698,-0.009116159,0.055180054,-0.020808203,-0.01623491,-0.051216442,0.11690994,0.07880119,-0.03723254,-0.07305209,0.006212219,0.051795598,-0.008653006,-0.015697889,0.040271048,-0.10525636,0.008076022,-0.024242125,0.064694956,-0.059989728,-0.002819955,-0.076144956,0.040520843,0.03529103,0.051919553,0.03442588,0.067899585,0.0128808785,0.056751184,0.07221822,-0.012407143,0.024951743,-0.0150902355,-0.028733885,0.017211305,0.004924227,0.035903748,-0.091373354,0.042948697,4.7465896e-33,0.011772024,0.031998288,-0.06583665,0.053121094,-0.0008326904,-0.04403785,0.015981501,0.010124052,-0.10467403,0.014865957,-0.06906916,-0.002294249,-0.026436051,0.052478693,0.039553333,-0.004036572,0.018441431,0.028246704,-0.07936259,0.015968854,0.07467864,-0.1158763,0.016350158,-0.061379205,0.057042137,0.0063154856,0.044035204,-0.016844034,-0.032817982,5.3409367e-06,-0.048182067,-0.0