c9c7589f-d899-44db-9a55-9122764dd4f9	safetyjudgmentguide_corpus_v20260423c	0	# AI Safety Judgment Guide **Corpus Document | Category: Methodology** **Retrieval targets: safety, data safety, red yellow green, what's safe, can I paste this, can I upload this, client data, PII, HIPAA, 42 CFR Part 2, case notes, is it okay to use AI for, privacy, confidential, identifying information, safe to share, enterprise agreement, de-identify, is this confidential, substance use, SUD records, immigration status, HMIS, mandated reporter, case management system** --- ## What This Framework Is Red / Yellow / Green is a decision framework for determining what's safe to put into an AI tool — and what isn't. It was developed for California county HHS managers who work in environments where a wrong data decision can compromise a case, violate a legal protection, or end a career. The framework teaches judgment, not rules. Rules tell you what to do in known situations. Judgment tells you what to do in the gray areas — and in HHS work, almost everything is a gray area. --- ## The Red / Yellow / Green Framework Most AI safety decisions in county HHS work fall into three categories: **Green — Relatively Safe.** The content doesn't identify individuals, doesn't contain protected information, and wouldn't cause harm if it were stored or surfaced by the AI platform. **Yellow — It Depends.** The content could be safe or risky depending on context, how it's used, what tool you're using, and what you've removed before pasting. This is where most of your real work lives. **Red — Do Not Use.** The content contains information that should never go into a general-purpose AI tool under any circumstances. --- ## Red: Content That Should Never Enter an AI Tool These should never be entered into AI tools like ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, or Copilot — regardless of how the tool	[-0.056463912,0.0673155,-0.07408247,-0.046704836,0.0642643,0.015011695,0.0939643,0.03834313,0.019783542,0.060639925,0.016496068,0.0215