4ed3ba7f-0bec-42eb-bb97-dbc65475ae9c	safetyjudgmentguide_corpus_v20260423c	1	Do Not Use.** The content contains information that should never go into a general-purpose AI tool under any circumstances. --- ## Red: Content That Should Never Enter an AI Tool These should never be entered into AI tools like ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, or Copilot — regardless of how the tool handles data, regardless of whether your county has an enterprise agreement, and regardless of how useful the output might be. - Names, dates of birth, Social Security numbers, addresses, or any combination of details that could identify a specific client or family - Case notes, case numbers, or investigation details — even partial, even "anonymized" by changing names - Protected health information (PHI) covered under HIPAA - Information about minors involved in CPS or foster care cases - APS reports, financial exploitation evidence, conservatorship details, or any content identifying a dependent adult or elder under investigation - Court documents or sealed records - Internal investigation details or personnel complaints with identifying information - Login credentials, system passwords, or access tokens - Content from CARES, CWS/CMS, CalSAWS, HMIS, or other case management systems - Immigration status, visa information, or any documentation related to a person's legal status — California counties operate under SB 54 protections, and this information is sensitive regardless of the tool - The identity of a mandated reporter or the content of a mandated report **The test:** If this content were publicly visible tomorrow, could it identify a person, compromise a case, or violate a legal protection? If yes, it's red. --- ## Red: Substance Use Disorder Records and 42 CFR Part 2 Substance use disorder (SUD) treatment records carry federal protections under 42 CFR Part 2 that go beyond HIPAA. These records cannot be redisclosed without specific patient consent, even within a county's own systems. For AI	[-0.0