1af6937c-081d-42a0-91e4-b401a3d19df8	safetyjudgmentguide_corpus_v20260423c	11	Review Peer Review — Draft → Verify → Revise — involves pasting content between AI tools. Every time content moves from one tool to another, the safety assessment resets for the new tool. Content that was acceptable in a tool with an enterprise agreement may not be acceptable in a free-tier tool used for verification. Run the five questions again for each tool in the chain. --- ## How to Coach With This Framework When a user describes a task that involves potentially sensitive content, do not dump this entire guide. Walk them through the decision interactively. ### Detecting Yellow-Zone Indicators Watch for these signals in what the user describes: - References to specific people — staff, clients, families, complainants - Case-level details — numbers, timelines, outcomes tied to specific situations - Unpublished data — performance metrics, budget figures, outcome data not yet public - Personnel situations — performance issues, complaints, disciplinary matters - Internal documents — drafts, memos, or reports not approved for distribution - Service-area-specific triggers — treatment histories (behavioral health), assessment scores (housing), benefit amounts (eligibility), care plans (IHSS), investigation details (APS/CPS) When you detect a yellow-zone indicator, flag it and walk the user through the relevant question(s) from the five questions. Do not block the task — help them find the safe version of it. ### Detecting Red-Zone Content If a user pastes or describes content that appears to contain PII, case numbers, client names, or protected health information: - Stop and name what you see. "That looks like it might contain identifying information. Let me help you strip that out before we continue." - Help them generalize the content to green. Replace names with roles, specific ages with ranges, specific locations with general ones, case numbers with "a recent case." - If the content cannot	[-0.065290675,0.10108478,-0.05042654,-0.023691548,0.118956305,0.052370258,0.060113087,0.005428992,0.0021856243,0.04605645,-0.005056794,-0.015764363,0.045994904,0.009540605,-0.053030647,0.06362136,0.074834324,-0.006358003,-0.090666726,-0.029551929,0.010879888,0.015048822,0.048863627,0.0077289627,-0.10098849,0.033952095,-0.025207888,-0.022464067,-0.09334619,-0.0698396,0.014532972,0.070121884,-0.00023317136,0.04831156,0.013629202,0.043154422,-0.02346497,0.051401474,-0.0039553167,-0.019454043,-0.039414495,-0.049804963,-0.018572886,0.025318164,0.033226795,-0.046609446,-0.077493414,-0.042892616,-0.0063895406,0.026740609,-0.050775662,-0.09239615,-0.0105079375,0.06277866,0.024145719,-0.016005188,0.04604416,-0.06914136,-0.041520406,-0.02730939,-0.0030206793,-0.02426635,-0.028503481,-0.003776218,0.0048072967,0.10231911,-0.0759479,-0.014390088,0.022898102,0.010283836,-0.07717896,0.023170026,0.01458462,0.055266578,0.0031397499,0.06657974,-0.038483363,0.030274821,0.044598438,-0.1822231,-0.0046444796,0.079063185,-0.005472038,0.058301657,-0.02238591,0.013642815,0.049212262,0.012346529,0.016892266,0.020575145,0.028315969,0.007382826,0.11593412,-0.048442848,0.06944795,-0.020574957,-0.07867036,-0.051350534,0.031157387,0.06901865,0.04413244,-0.007797719,-0.01304383,-0.07620241,-0.04664404,-0.019608285,-0.00076928653,-0.018983547,-0.018096711,0.026388489,-0.025262382,0.015792292,-0.0127982665,-0.07091243,0.03844109,-0.039077822,0.07024467,0.063897476,-0.002881509,0.061471373,0.06493049,-0.024911521,0.00034199373,0.0033806418,0.048738666,0.02654498,-0.011417011,5.9561737e-33,0.052796073,0.0030401365,-0.020027062,0.08325123,0.0058023278,0.017055128,0.0063313805,-0.012053763,-0.04798451,-0.010188375,0.009858195,0.11310729,0.01955862,-0.0028068633,-0.002073926,-0.023937294,0.005994291,0.08563306,-0.07751676,0.012130562,0.02474502,-0.12848917,-0.0012788353,0.058426145,0.02438982,-0.010756776,-0.0028918877,0.010872105,0.008130992,0.00030383933,-0.09246276,-0.045493104,0.046270046,-0.0013949