c0d9b7e1-3cb3-44b0-b6b2-545af7770dc3	cmf_corpus_taskchain_v20260424b	11	external enough. **Example transition:** "The [service area] landscape is experiencing [change description]..." **What to avoid:** - Internal challenges ("Our staff are overwhelmed" — that's internal, controllable) - Vague trends ("Things are changing fast") - Forces that don't connect to the change in Step 4 **Coaching check:** For each force, ask: "Can the audience make this go away through their own decisions?" If yes, it's internal, not external. --- ## The Two Most Common Errors These are not minor coaching notes. They are the two errors that persist even after extensive coaching — even after two days of in-person workshop instruction. The coach should expect these errors to surface repeatedly, re-check for them every time any part of the message changes, and normalize the difficulty when correcting them. --- ### Error 1: Negative Language in Step 2 **What it looks like:** - Judgmental words: "outdated," "reactive," "siloed," "limited," "manual" - Qualifier words that imply inadequacy: "only," "just," "merely" - Dependency framing: "relying on," "depending on," "defaulting to" - Describing absences instead of actions: "Counties aren't using data to inform placement decisions" - Implied criticism that technically avoids forbidden words but still carries a sting **Why it happens:** People are trained by conventional problem-solution frameworks to set up the pain first. They instinctively want to show what's broken so the solution feels necessary. This framework deliberately does not do that — but the habit runs deep. **Why it's destructive:** Negative language in Step 2 activates status quo bias. The audience stops listening to the message and starts defending their practices. The entire purpose of Step 2 — getting the audience to nod and say "yeah, that's about right" — is lost. Once defense is triggered, Steps 3–5 land on closed ears. **The coaching move:** When someone uses negative language, redirect gently. When	[-0.016285218,0.024749814,0.08925886,0.007512143,0.07495579,-0.03632102,0.038110882,0.036424864,0.05665649,0.0037697523,0.023854414,-0.045555495,0.0248108,0.018124616,0.014414686,0.00843625,0.06763889,0.0005062693,-0.09292209,0.0065331287,-0.005252733,0.0049859853,-0.022970587,0.065533504,-0.08892517,0.020934582,-0.08954055,-0.04992112,-0.0330101,-0.0635147,-0.06608426,0.05636062,-0.019350288,0.033202585,0.0069400277,0.09394057,-0.03417933,0.071005166,-0.07106447,-0.027917488,-0.04786272,-0.012462065,-0.020620743,-0.035558935,0.00022067646,-0.07250947,-0.032645516,-0.028108208,-0.06274357,-0.036323167,-0.10699067,-0.03694987,0.04991244,0.010382302,0.04295409,0.0074332412,0.11281758,0.11179224,-0.032814622,0.06267791,0.025851993,-0.061500307,-0.113717966,-0.008730623,-0.009623846,0.045066074,-0.024156077,0.011927541,-0.016348325,0.08483443,-0.024176393,-0.042154063,0.019781139,-0.023624139,0.06573793,0.06276499,-0.012292517,0.014143143,0.08920307,-0.13789108,0.0053007943,0.0069288323,-0.0027886159,0.02150298,0.012598627,-0.039940782,0.00926725,-0.005796119,0.06227392,0.051365074,-0.0059850276,-0.07273977,-0.01650128,0.025056262,0.12993445,0.050697774,-0.06749001,-0.045254156,-0.03007389,0.059151247,0.0068690055,0.011948285,-0.017844943,-0.052579477,-0.023621319,-0.069989234,-0.03300357,-0.021216502,-0.07489337,-0.0072351396,-0.07956362,-0.011865687,-0.01537201,-0.052346464,0.018399552,0.008444055,0.047404587,0.019357491,-0.05793903,0.061810125,0.011660803,0.004770212,0.012092204,-0.027644388,0.06559473,-0.0054168627,0.00048119604,5.116458e-33,0.047579806,-0.0019045323,-0.033569574,0.058655918,0.022594173,-0.047009807,-0.01066836,-0.015040844,0.012533381,-0.016019806,0.12099182,0.04355534,0.041299634,-0.017171238,0.0444761,-0.006514812,-0.055055603,0.02386448,-0.026576277,0.025701528,0.059748992,0.01889641,-0.03283349,-0.03999734,-0.027389184,0.020017369,-0.025026865,0.0011323028,-0.023968242,0.014392517,-0.059300173,-0.060533218,-0.018585041