3725af92-fc1b-4b1d-adf8-fe4676fa9c52	taskchain_acl_adaptive_v20260424a	0	# ACL Breakdown — Adaptive Output **Corpus Document | Category: Task Chain** **Retrieval targets: director summary, executive briefing, board memo, fiscal impact, staff briefing, frontline, train staff, what do I tell my workers** --- ## What This Document Does The core ACL task chain (TaskChain_ACL_Base) produces a breakdown for program managers and supervisors — the primary audience. This document handles two additional output modes triggered by how the user asks, plus routing logic for common variations. --- ## Director / Deputy Director Mode Triggered when the user's language signals an executive audience: "my director needs," "brief the board," "fiscal impact," "what's the risk," "do I need county counsel," "executive summary," "bottom line." Produce this output instead of (or in addition to) the standard breakdown: **Executive summary**: 3 sentences maximum. What this ACL does, what it means for the county, what the timeline is. No jargon. No regulatory citations. **Fiscal impact**: Does this ACL create new costs — staffing, training, system changes, expanded caseloads, new forms or notices? Is funding provided through the ACL or existing allocations? If the ACL addresses funding, state the amount and source. If it doesn't address cost, say so explicitly and recommend the county's fiscal unit assess independently. Reference CWDA fiscal analyses if the topic is one CWDA has weighed in on. **Board / county counsel action**: Answer each yes, no, or unclear with a one-line explanation: - Does this require a county plan amendment? - Does the plan amendment require Board of Supervisors approval? (Not all do — some are administrative.) - Does this require a budget modification? - Does this require county counsel review? **Compliance risk**: What happens if the county doesn't implement on time? State and federal funding implications, audit exposure, legal liability. If the ACL doesn't state consequences, say so — but	[-0.08535804,-0.022372827,0.007806158,0.047983345,0.031590108,0.032828175,-0.011186733,-0.00014780517,0.049906597,0.018556891,0.0265356,-0.016403526,0.0036130627,-0.021800311,-0.035098106,0.070236504,0.112550154,0.0011489955,-0.09916564,0.020493861,0.13669048,0.027295804,-0.03423273,0.012375804,-0.060725305,-0.028362846,-0.07584155,-0.049108744,-0.07891974,-0.056569632,0.00924396,0.05557892,0.053021085,0.022241851,0.055974472,0.014975754,0.06627141,0.027718747,0.04613549,0.0037347989,-0.08368125,0.03368045,0.0008300226,0.066562995,-0.07870363,-0.090850845,0.0034060904,-0.07980726,-0.09223068,0.053403027,-0.011336004,0.037768118,0.012392943,0.08068552,0.0007011198,-0.023502748,-0.028065115,-0.022267804,-0.07304065,-0.014778768,-0.092882216,0.016164627,-0.08549785,-0.0032465842,0.0034135787,0.01900909,-0.052076124,-0.027194519,-0.03555546,-0.019104106,-0.043871164,-0.044182833,0.0043600826,-0.048251193,0.04601978,0.014277541,-0.00030933315,0.061915588,0.08239582,-0.15721564,-0.026110979,0.07582793,0.020018855,-0.031773604,-0.022912936,-0.026902907,0.020934457,0.04153359,-0.0026518046,0.05362091,0.07798236,-0.044233937,0.084742986,-0.07088237,0.037835408,0.0015967683,-0.002724668,-0.084801115,0.024986241,0.062439524,0.034360513,-0.019217579,0.010389132,-0.082006484,-0.027522495,-0.049265344,0.013061805,0.011949072,-0.04440173,0.027088821,0.069082074,-0.009939563,-0.037663322,-0.056127697,0.021373797,0.0005613187,-0.0050738975,-0.0052210647,0.0547672,0.01384747,-0.02157387,-0.012624265,0.0034118125,0.049389757,0.08304883,-0.040423464,-0.02866014,1.7017472e-33,0.0072238487,-0.009570697,-0.015200196,0.027274037,0.016131284,0.003195484,0.03078787,-0.01195681,0.01729968,0.022405468,0.004895067,0.09565713,-0.010584443,-0.023923837,-0.02898548,-0.052624565,-0.05226613,0.052352477,-0.050823167,0.07554324,0.029059116,-0.018480144,0.01778819,-0.008494942,0.02567293,-0.03821487,-0.016777623,-0.004981345,-0.049907535,0.026291339,-0.009416755,-0.017335279,0.08