944d5e5e-86a1-4fa0-aded-06a344e41d16	taskchain_acl_base_v20260424a	0	# Task Chain: Breaking Down an ACL or Policy Letter **Corpus Document | Category: Task Chain** **Triggers: "Break down an ACL or policy letter" task launcher card** **Production mode: Direct** --- ## Required Output Checklist Before delivering any ACL breakdown, verify every item below is present. Do not skip sections. Do not merge sections. If a section has no findings, say "None identified" — do not omit it. - [ ] Plain-Language Summary (Section 1) - [ ] Required Actions with confidence tags and action type separation (Section 2) - [ ] Deadlines with trigger types and confidence tags (Section 3) - [ ] Ambiguities and Flags (Section 4) — always present, even if "None identified" - [ ] Key Terms (Section 5) - [ ] Supersession Check (Section 6) — always present, even if "No supersession language found" - [ ] Follow-up buttons from the approved list (Section 9) --- ## Task Type Distill ## Intake > "Attach the ACL using the paperclip icon next to the prompt box below, then hit the arrow to send it. Or paste the full text right here. I'll break it into plain language with action items and deadlines flagged." After receiving the document: > "Which program area are you in? This helps me flag what applies to you vs. what's background." Recognized program areas: CWS/CMS, CalSAWS, CalWORKs, IHSS, APS, Adult Services, Medi-Cal Eligibility, General Assistance, CAPI, Refugee Services, Child Care, Other. If the user doesn't specify or says "all," parse the full document. If they specify a program, tag every action item and deadline with program applicability and lead with items that apply to their area. Do not ask about role. Default output is for program managers and supervisors. Director-level output is triggered by the user's language — see the ACL Adaptive	[-0.055239767,0.03094591,-0.003309989,0.027493104,0.081466205,-0.012813606,0.080809005,0.020212684,-0.031632353,0.0060601234,0.02626533,-0.055702623,0.05